  "summary": "After returning home at 6:00 am, Bondel wakes at 9:30 am and calls Jimmy Sexton, who is preparing for an autopsy. She requests that he drive her to Chimney House to meet the county police chief. During the drive, Bondel recounts the mysterious events she has witnessed, including the involvement of an international gang and a secret meeting involving a Russian, an American, a British man, and a mysterious woman. She notes a German presence, specifically mentioning that Bauer, the butler, attempted to obtain a report regarding Chimney House, which Jimmy suspects is linked to the death of Gerry Wade.\n\nThe conversation turns to Hel Eberhard, a German inventor who has applied for a patent on a steel technology capable of revolutionizing aviation by making objects stronger and lighter. Bondel explains that Eberhard plans to bring his formula to an unofficial meeting at the Double Dragon Church, which will include Sir Oswald Kutt and the aviation minister. The \"Seven-Faced Clock\" group intends to steal this formula, which a Russian claimed is worth millions. Bondel also reveals that Ronnie's final words were, \"Seven-Faced Clock, tell Jimmy Sessage.\" Jimmy concludes that a messenger named Paul was likely responsible for Mr. Grey's death. Upon arriving at Chimney House, they meet Major Melrose and attend an inquest. Bondel and the doctor testify, and the death is officially ruled an accident caused by someone playing with a gun.",
